Rep. Debbie Wasserman Schultz (D-Fla.) asked individuals on Twitter to name their “favorite” Democratic policy — many replied, but it’s unlikely the response was what she hoped for.

Democrats have led on so many great policies. Which is your favorite? Tell us the one that makes you most proud! → http://t.co/dJ0qKyZmAg — D Wasserman Schultz (@DWStweets) March 13, 2015

After the DNC chair tweeted her question, individuals on Twitter immediately started to poke fun at the question.

Some skewered the Democratic Party for recent email scandals, while others took aim at President Franklin D. Roosevelt’s internment of Japanese Americans.

Error 404. File not found RT @DWStweets: Democrats have led on so many great policies. Which is your favorite? — Matthew (@Matthops82) March 13, 2015

@DWStweets giving ambassadorships to donors — ellis wyatt (@smbubba) March 13, 2015

@DWStweets The one where you destroyed so much of our country. Oh wait. That would be all of them. — Tim Butler (@tijfbutler) March 13, 2015

@DWStweets Keeping poor people poor so they'll vote Democrat seems to work really well. — DCinAZ (@DCinAZ) March 13, 2015

Criminal destruction of evidence. RT @DWStweets: Democrats have led on so many great policies. Which is your favorite? — Logan Act Scholar (@JohnEkdahl) March 13, 2015

@DWStweets When FDR made Japanese go into internment camps — Blake Pine (@LetsBanEvrythng) March 13, 2015

@DWStweets Right off the top of my head, I'd say incessant cover ups and lies. Oh wait, you said proud of, not disgusted with. — Pam Sands (@pam_sands) March 13, 2015

The Syrian red line. RT @DWStweets: Democrats have led on so many great policies. Which is your favorite? — Phineas Fahrquar (@irishspy) March 13, 2015

